17 (5) "Disciplinary literacy" means a literacy instructional approach that
18 teaches students how to use literacy to think, interpret text, and engage in advanced
19 participation and conversations like a disciplinary expert would.
20 (6) "Student" means a student in grades four through eight.
21 (7) "Teacher" means each fourth through eighth grade teacher who teaches
22 reading or English language arts.
